\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Findings,
 Classification,
 and Routing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall classify audit findings,
 self-assessment results,
 and control test outcomes using a three-tier scheme.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Conforming
\series default
:
 The assessed control is implemented correctly,
 is operating as intended,
 and is producing the desired outcome.
 Conforming findings shall be recorded in the Control Testing Register and shall contribute to the maturity scoring process under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Observation
\series default
:
 A minor gap,
 inconsistency,
 or area for improvement that does not constitute a material failure of the control's protective or operational function.
 The Assistant IT Director shall document and track observations.
 The Assistant IT Director shall reclassify observations that recur across two (2) or more consecutive assessment cycles as deficiencies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Deficiency
\series default
:
 The control is not implemented,
 is not operating as intended,
 or is not producing the desired outcome,
 and the gap creates material risk to the security,
 compliance,
 or operational posture of the Department.
 The Assistant IT Director shall route deficiencies to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 for corrective action plan development within ten (10) business days of classification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When a deficiency affects a control implementing a CJIS Security Policy requirement,
 the IT Director shall evaluate whether the deficiency constitutes a reportable condition under the applicable CJIS notification obligations and shall act accordingly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When an audit or assessment reveals that non-compliance by an individual has occurred,
 the Assistant IT Director shall route the finding to the IT Director for evaluation under the enforcement framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
