plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall prepare a consolidated Annual Audit Summary Report at the conclusion of each annual audit cycle.
 The report shall document:
 the total number of assessments conducted by type (internal audit,
 self-assessment,
 and control test);
 the number and distribution of findings by classification tier;
 the policies and controls with open deficiencies;
 trend data comparing current-year results to prior-year results;
 and recommendations for the next annual cycle.
 The Assistant IT Director shall submit the Annual Audit Summary Report to the IT Director and shall make it available as an input to the annual policy review and maturity scoring process under 
\series bold
Policy 
